The body of former Rongo university student, the late  Sharon Otieno has finally been collected from the mortuary and taken to her parent’s home in Magare village in Homa Bay county ahead of her burial this Friday. The late Sharon whose death is now  the centre of  sizzling court battle involving Migori governor  was found brutally murdered on September 3rd and her body dumped in Kodera forest. And as Victor Oloo reports, according to Luo customs, Sharon who had separated from her husband will not be buried  n her parents compound but will instead be laid to rest at her paternal grandfather’s homestead.   